From: Nicolai Buchwitz <nb@tiber.science>
Date: Mon, 10 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: broadcom: disable AutogrEEEn and EEE on BCM54xx

The BCM54213PE (and other BCM54xx) PHY defaults to AutogrEEEn mode,
which causes the PHY to autonomously enter Low Power Idle (LPI) state.
When paired with a MAC that does not support EEE (like Cadence GEM/macb
on RPi5/CM5/RP1), this leads to silent packet loss and eventual network
death because the MAC cannot handle the LPI transitions.

Even with AutogrEEEn disabled and the PHY switched to Native EEE mode,
EEE is still advertised during autonegotiation. If the link partner
negotiates EEE and sends LPI frames, the MACB MAC cannot process
incoming LPI on the RGMII interface, causing the TX queue to stall and
resulting in DNS resolution timeouts and other connectivity loss.

Disable AutogrEEEn mode during PHY init and suppress EEE advertisement
entirely via phy_disable_eee() so that EEE is never negotiated.

Based on the fix from raspberrypi/linux PR #7270 by Nicolai Buchwitz.

Signed-off-by: Nicolai Buchwitz <nb@tiber.science>
---
 drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 include/linux/brcmphy.h    |  3 +++
 2 files changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c b/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c
--- a/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c
@@ -487,6 +487,18 @@ static int bcm54xx_config_init(struct phy_device *phydev)
 		bcm_phy_write_shadow(phydev, BCM54XX_SHD_RGMII_MODE, 0);
 
 
+	/* Disable AutogrEEEn and switch to Native EEE mode so the MAC
+	 * can control LPI signaling and observe RX LPI on the RGMII
+	 * interface.
+	 */
+	err = bcm_phy_modify_exp(phydev, BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_MII_BUF_CNTL0,
+				 BCM54XX_MII_BUF_CNTL0_AUTOGREEEN_EN, 0);
+	if (err)
+		return err;
+
+	/* Do not advertise EEE — the MACB/GEM MAC cannot handle LPI. */
+	phy_disable_eee(phydev);
+
 	bcm54xx_adjust_rxrefclk(phydev);
 
 	switch (phydev->drv->phy_id & PHY_ID_MATCH_MODEL_MASK) {
diff --git a/include/linux/brcmphy.h b/include/linux/brcmphy.h
--- a/include/linux/brcmphy.h
+++ b/include/linux/brcmphy.h
@@ -187,6 +187,9 @@
 #define BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_IDDQ_SR		(1 << 3)
 
 #define BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_LED_CTL		(MII_BCM54XX_EXP_SEL_TOP + 0x0C)
+#define BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_MII_BUF_CNTL0		(MII_BCM54XX_EXP_SEL_TOP + 0x00)
+#define BCM54XX_MII_BUF_CNTL0_AUTOGREEEN_EN	BIT(0)
+
 #define  BCM54XX_LED4_SEL_INTR			BIT(1)
 
 /*
